1. the microgrid system that do not surf the Net that is incorporated into the power networks is characterized in that, comprises distributed generation system, distributed energy-storage system, user load and microgrid central controller;
      Said distributed generation system and distributed energy-storage system insert the low-voltage alternating-current bus through energy conversion devices separately, and the low-voltage alternating-current bus inserts the high-voltage alternating bus through step-up transformer again; User load inserts the high-voltage alternating bus with the mode of dividing into groups through step-up transformer; The high-voltage alternating bus inserts public electric wire net through the points of common connection single-point; The points of common connection place is provided with static switch;
      Said microgrid central controller is connected through the cable communication with distributed generation system, distributed energy-storage system and static switch.

